title: UN: "Humanitarian situation in the eastern Donbas is extremely alarming" | Ukraine latest
description: The United Nations' humanitarian agency OCHA raised concerns that the humanitarian conditions in eastern Ukraine continue to deteriorate four months into the Russian invasion. "Nearly four months since the start of the war, the humanitarian situation across Ukraine â€” particularly in the eastern Donbas â€” is extremely alarming and continues to deteriorate rapidly," the OCHA said in a statement. The situation in the key city of Sievierodonetsk, where heavy fighting has been taking place in recent weeks, is "particularly worrying," the OCHA added. Ukrainian officials have said that thousands of civilians remain in the city, with hundreds sheltering in a local chemical plant.  According to the OCHA, the UN and its partners have delivered aid to more than 8.8 million people across Ukraine since the Russian invasion started. |In a regular intelligence report, the British Defense Ministry said Russia was increasingly cracking down on opposition to the war. "In Russia, the war has accelerated the stateâ€™s long-term trajectory towards authoritarianism," the report said. Citing migration applications, the ministry said some 15,000 Russian millionaires were likely trying to leave the country. It added that the so-called Freedom for Russia Legion, which includes Russians fighting on Ukraine's side, has "almost certainly deployed in combat alongside the Ukrainian military." The report noted that Russia's parliament was working to introduce a 20-year sentence for Russians who fight against the Russia.|The European Commission is due to recommend granting EU candidate status to Ukraineand Moldova later on Friday. Candidate status is not the same as EU membership â€” it denotes the start of an often lengthy process toward joining the bloc. The Commission will give its opinion on the matter to the EU's 27 members after an agreement on the opinion in a meeting Friday, and the decision is expected to be made public next week. The bloc's governments will then have to decide how to proceed. On Thursday, German Chancellor Olaf Scholz, Italian Prime Minister Mario Draghi, French President Emmanuel Macron and Romanian President Klaus Iohannis said in Kyiv that they backed Ukraine's application for EU candidate status. Ukraine and Moldova will likely face a long accession process. For Ukraine, the focus of the process will be on promoting good governance, the rule of law and measures to tackle corruption. Ukraine's President Volodymyr Zelensky submitted Ukraine's bid for EU membership shortly after the war started in February.|Subscribe: https://www.youtube.com/user/deutschewelleenglish?sub_confirmation=1|For more news go to: http://www.dw.com/en/|Follow DW on social media:|â–ºFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/deutschewellenews/|â–ºTwitter: https://twitter.com/dwnews|â–ºInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/dwnews|FÃ¼r Videos in deutscher Sprache besuchen Sie: https://www.youtube.com/dwdeutsch|#Ukraine #Russia #Lysychansk

title: Berkunjung ke Borobudur, Presiden Jerman Apresiasi Pemerintah Indonesia Soal Konservasi Candi
description: MAGELANG, KOMPAS.TV - Presiden Republik Federal Jerman, Frank Walter Steinmeier, Jumat siang, mengunjungi kawasan wisata Candi Borobudur, Magelang, Jawa Tengah.||||Rombongan Presiden Jerman, Frank Walter Steinmeier, tiba di kompleks wisata Candi Borobudur sekitar pukul 09.45 WIB.||||Rombongan Presiden Jerman selanjutnya melihat kondisi candi, dan menyempatkan untuk naik ke Candi Borobudur.||||Baca Juga Soal Foto Stupa Borobudur Mirip Jokowi, Wamenag: Simbol Agama Jangan Dijadikan Bahan Olokan di https://www.kompas.tv/article/299947/soal-foto-stupa-borobudur-mirip-jokowi-wamenag-simbol-agama-jangan-dijadikan-bahan-olokan||||Menurut Dirjen Kebudayaan Kemdikbud Ristek, Hilmar Farid, Presiden Jerman merasa takjub dengan kemegahan Candi Borobudur, dan mengapresiasi pemerintah Indonesia yang telah melakukan konservasi candi dengan baik.||||Selain itu, dibahas pula tentang pertukaran teknologi Jerman-Indonesia untuk upaya konservasi Candi Borobudur.||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/300138/berkunjung-ke-borobudur-presiden-jerman-apresiasi-pemerintah-indonesia-soal-konservasi-candi

title: Israel woos Modi Govt ahead of first West Asian QUAD summit | Decoding Indiaâ€™s role in I2U2
description: Ahead of the West Asian Quad summit, Israeli PM Naftali Bennett is set to visit India in a bid to strengthen ties. The first of its kind I2U2 virtual summit will be held next month. Prime Minister Narendra Modi, US President Joe Biden, Israeli Prime Minister Neftali Bennett and UAE President Mohammed bin Zayed Al Nahyan would attend summit for discussions of the food security crisis and other areas of cooperation. As per White House, the summit is part of the Biden administration's efforts to re-energise and revitalise American alliances across the world. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.|About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:|--------------------------------------------------------------------|The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Shailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi / Raj Anadkat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. title: The Truth About England & Gareth Southgate

title: Russian MSTA-S Howitzers strike Ukraine positions as Zelensky seeks modern weapons from the West
description: Russian forces struck Ukrainian positions with MSTA-S self propelled Howitzers in eastern Ukraine. The Russian defence ministry shared footage of a Russian crew carrying out a firing mission. Russia has been using MSTA-S self propelled howitzers to target the Ukraine positions. Russia claims its MSTA-S Howitzer fire destroyed camouflaged positions of the Ukraine troops. Russia has been inflicting heavy casualties on Ukraine in the ongoing fighting in eastern region of the country. title: â€˜Agnipathâ€™ arson blazes through Bihar; Train coaches gutted by fire in Ballia | Day 3 of protest
description: The protests over Modi government's new defence recruitment policy - Agnipath spilled onto day 3, with army aspirants continuing to stage protests across railway stations in Bihar. Train coaches at Mohiuddinnagar, Lakhisarai, Samastipur railway stations were set ablaze. Protesters even blocked railway tracks with burning tyres. In Uttar Pradesh's Ballia too, agitators set trains on fire. The protests continued even as the centre announced a one-time waiver on age limit. The centre had also busted 'myths' about the policy on Thursday. Watch this video to find out how the Agnipath fire is spreading through Bihar. |#bihar #agnipath #protest #vandal #train #railways #agniveer #defenceforces #armedforces #india #uttarpradesh #ballia

title: Kizhi Parotta Recipe in Tamil | Banana Leaf Parotta | Street food Recipe in Tamil
description: In this video we will see how to make kizhi parotta recipe in tamil. In this recipe, parottas are soaked in salna and layered with a spicy chicken masala and wrapped in a banana leaf. Then they are cooked in high heat, the parottas and the masala gets steamed inside the banana leaf and the parottas are completely soaked with the flavor from the masala. Kizhi parottas are a new street food style and they can be made with a wide variety of fillings.|#kizhiparotta #kizhiporotta #streetfoodtamil |Friends, please do try this kizhi parotta recipe at home and share it with your friends and family. title: Roy Suryo Datangi Polda: Mau Klarifikasi Soal Meme Stupa Mirip Jokowi
description: JAKARTA, KOMPAS.TV - Roy Suryo mendatangi Polda Metro Jaya bersama kuasa hukum, melaporkan 3 akun yang diduga mengedit dan menyebarluaskan pertama kali terkait dengan postingan plesetan Candi Borobudur.||||Roy Suryo datang ke Mapolda Metro Jaya, Kamis (16/6/2022) malam dengan membawa barang bukti berupa tangkapan layar dan tautan 3 akun yang diduga memposting pertama kali postingannya terkait Candi Borobudur.||||Baca Juga Temui Warga di Surabaya, Puan Maharani Diteriaki "Presiden" di https://www.kompas.tv/article/299940/temui-warga-di-surabaya-puan-maharani-diteriaki-presiden||||Roy Suryo manyatakan, tak ada niat menghina pihak mana pun termasuk umat Buddha akibat meme Candi Borobudur yang menimbulkan kegaduhan ini.||||Roy mengaku ia bukan pengunggah apalagi pengedit pertama meme tersebut dan hanya merespons saat akunnya di taut ke cuitan yang menampilkan meme foto stupa Candi Borobudur yang diedit mirip Presiden Jokowi.|| ||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/299946/roy-suryo-datangi-polda-mau-klarifikasi-soal-meme-stupa-mirip-jokowi

Saya minta maaf ke seluruh umat Buddha atau masyarakat yang tekrnea imbas dari kasus ini, Gara-gara ada provokasi. title: The Missing Sisters Part 1 | Crime Patrol Dial 100 | Full Episode
description: Click here to Subscribe to SET India: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCpEhnqL0y41EpW2TvWAHD7Q?sub_confirmation=1|Click here to watch full episodes of Crime Patrol Satark Season 2:  https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupx-Ii958bn2-dYO2vE3tdmX|Episode 538: The Missing Sisters Part 1|--------------------|The case of the missing sisters continues with a shocking find made by the police. The police find a dead body in a water tank and suspect that the dead person is related to Sushasini, the mother of Shristi and Mishti. title: Polisi: Sekolah Khilafatul Muslimin Tolak Pancasila & Larang Muridnya Hormati Bendera Merah Putih
description: KOMPAS.TV - Polisi menyatakan Khilafatul Muslimin memiliki Lembaga Pendidikan untuk proses kaderisasi di organisasinya.||||Sekolah yang didirikan melarang muridnya memberi penghormatan terhadap bendera merah putih dan menentang pancasila.||||Polisi menyebut Khilafatul Muslimin memiliki 31 unit Lembaga Pendidikan di sejumlah daerah.||||Dalam proses pendidikannya, para murid diminta untuk tidak mengakui pemerintah.||||Semua Lembaga Pendidikan Khilafatul Muslimin tidak mengacu pada Undang -Undang Sistem Pendidkan Nasional.||||Baca Juga Atribut Khilafatul Muslimin di Kampung Khilafah Dicopot di https://www.kompas.tv/article/299181/atribut-khilafatul-muslimin-di-kampung-khilafah-dicopot||||Khilafatul Muslimin memberikan pendidikan gratis kepada anak-anak anggotanya setelah mereka dibaiat.||||Sementara itu, Pusat Pelaporan dan Analisis Transaksi Keuangan, PPATK telah membekukan 21 rekening yang tekait dengan Khilafatul Muslimin.||||Tujuannya untuk mempermudah penyidik mendalami  aliran dana organisasi Khilafatul Muslimin yang sedang disidik Polda Metro Jaya.||||Soal nominal dana pada 21 rekening tersebut, Direktur Analisis PPATK Maryanto menyebut saldonya tidak signifikan.|| ||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/299908/polisi-sekolah-khilafatul-muslimin-tolak-pancasila-larang-muridnya-hormati-bendera-merah-putih

title: Jawab Keponakan Prabowo Soal Enggak Jadi Wamen Saat Reshuffle Rabu Kabinet Jokowi
description: JAKARTA, KOMPAS.TV  Pada reshuffle kabinet Rabu (15/6/2022) ada 2 menteri yang dilantik Presiden Jokowi.||||Muncul nama politikus Gerindra Rahayu Saraswati Djojohadikusumo yang juga digadang akan menempati posisi Wakil Menteri Koperasi dan UKM. ||||Namun tiba pada hari Rabu, tidak ada nama Rahayu dan kemunculannya di istana. ||||Lewat akun Instagramnya keponakan Prabowo Subianto itu pun memberikan unggahan terkait berita dirinya dipanggil ke Istana. ||||Baca Juga Momen Mesra Jokowi Jalan Bareng Para Ketum Partai Sebelum Reshuffle Kabinet, Sempat Atur Barisan di https://www.kompas.tv/article/299449/momen-mesra-jokowi-jalan-bareng-para-ketum-partai-sebelum-reshuffle-kabinet-sempat-atur-barisan||||"Kemarin dikira ke istana padahal ke studio untuk take vocal,"tulis Rahayu di salah satu unggahan feed Instagramnya. ||||Presiden Jokowi telah melantik Zulkifli Hasan dan mantan Panglima TNI Hadi Tjahjanto serta tiga wakil menteri lainnya di Istana Negara, Jakarta Pusat, Rabu (15/6/2022).||||Sedangkan untuk posisi Wakil Menteri:||||1. Dewan Pembina PSI Raja Juli Antoni sebagai Wakil Menteri ATR /BPN||||2. John Wempi Watipo sebagai Wakil Menteri Dalam Negeri (Wamendagri)||||3. Sekjen PBB Afriansyah Noor sebagai Wakil Menteri Tenaga Kerja (Wamenaker)||||Video Editor: Agung|| ||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/299901/jawab-keponakan-prabowo-soal-enggak-jadi-wamen-saat-reshuffle-rabu-kabinet-jokowi

title: WATCH LIVE: FL v Danielle Redlick - Wife On Trial For Murder Day 6
description: A woman stands trial for allegedly murdering her stepfather-turned-husband, and giving authorities a flimsy story about him stabbing himself and having a heart attack. Danielle Redlick, 48, faces a count death of second-degree murder, and tampering with evidence for allegedly killing Michael Redlick, 65. |The backstory between the couple is patently complicated. Michaelâ€™s second wife was actually Danielleâ€™s mother. They allegedly married in the first place to get her better health coverage as she was dying of cancer.|â€œIn fairness to Mike, Danielleâ€™s mother was dying of cancer when they were dating,â€ an unidentified family friend told WFTV. â€œShe had terrible insurance.â€|The account is that he fell in love with Danielle after her mother died. They married, with Danielle becoming his third wife.|The union ended in bloodshed. Danielle Redlick called 911 the morning of Jan. 12, 2019. She allegedly told police that her husband got angry on the night of Jan. 11, took a bite out of her McDonaldâ€™s burger, and spit it at her face. He allegedly grabbed, pushed her to the ground, and rubbed his fist against her face while shoving her head to a stove, she allegedly said. This culminated in her grabbing a knife, but he grabbed it, and made â€œstabbing motionsâ€ at himself. She allegedly claimed to try to hide in the bathroom, while her husband was at the door apparently referencing the movie Cape Fear.|She claimed to find him outside in the living room, badly hurt, cops said. Defendant Redlick allegedly claimed she tried to save him using CPR. She couldnâ€™t find her phone to call the police, and she collapsed in exhaustion next to Michael, she said. Danielle woke up the next morning, and finally called 911, she allegedly said.|But authorities said she was on a dating app about two hours before calling 911. The state of Michaelâ€™s body also allegedly didnâ€™t match her story. Contrary to her account, an investigator said they found no signs of Michael vomiting, and that the bruising on his left arm was consistent with defensive wounds. title: WATCH:â€˜This is constitutional mischief,â€™ Luttig says of Trump pressure on Pence to overturn election
description: J. He focused on the false claim from Trump legal adviser John Eastman that the vice president had the power to overturn a presidential election and how that false notion drove the pressure campaign to get former Vice President Mike Pence to declare Trump as president though Joe Biden was the declared winner.|â€œThis is constitutional mischief,â€ Luttig said.|The hearing was the third of several planned by the Jan. 6 committee that focused on Trumpâ€™s efforts to pressure former Vice President Mike Pence to reject Congress' official count of Electoral College votes on the day of the attack. title: Climate change threat in Congo as vast carbon-rich peat slab faces development - BBC News
description: In central Africa a giant slab of carbon-rich peat land, discovered by a team of British and Congolese scientists, is under threat from oil companies and farming.|The carbon must be kept in the ground to avoid accelerating climate change, but some plots have already been sold for oil exploration.   | |The Republic of Congo is also planning to develop the land for agriculture, unless richer nations deliver more financial assistance. |Huw Edwards presents BBC News at Ten reporting by Andrew Harding in Congo.|Please subscribe HERE http://bit.ly/1rbfUog|#BBCNews

title: Bodycam Video Shows Police Shootout During Traffic Stop In Florida
description: The Orlando Police Department released bodycam footage showing a shootout between police and a suspect during a traffic stop. The suspect allegedly opened fire on the officers as soon as they exited their cruisers, prompting the officers to fire back. The suspect fled in his vehicle after being hit by gunfire and crashed while fleeing. Officers arrived at the scene of the crash before calling for medical assistance to treat the wounded suspect. Neither of the officers were injured during the shootout. title: WATCH: Trump tweet attacking Pence was like â€˜pouring gasoline on the fire,â€™ White House aide says
description: During a Jan. 6 committee hearing on June 16, the committee played edited testimony from witnesses present in the White House as the Jan. 6 Capitol attack was underway.|The committee laid out how former Vice President Mike Pence came within 40 feet of rioters in the Capitol building while he was being evacuated. Just moments before, President Donald Trump sent out a tweet criticizing Pence for not taking action to overturn the election results.|According to testimony played during the hearing, former White House deputy press secretary Sarah Matthews testified that she and others believed â€œthat was the last thing that needed to be tweeted.â€|â€œThe situation was already bad. So it felt like he was pouring gasoline on the fire,â€ she said in the committeeâ€™s presentation.|Rep. Pete Aguilar, D-Calif., said Trumpâ€™s tweet inflamed the crowd.|â€œOur investigation found immediately after the 2:24 p.m. tweet, the crowds outside of the Capitol and inside the Capitol surged. The crowds inside the Capital were able to overwhelm law enforcement and the vice president was quickly evacuated from his ceremonial office to a secure location within the complex,â€ he said.|The hearing was the third of several planned by the Jan. 6 committee that focused on Trumpâ€™s efforts to pressure former Vice President Mike Pence to reject Congress' official count of Electoral College votes on the day of the attack. In the year since its creation, the committee has conducted more than 1,000 interviews, seeking critical information and documents from people witness to, or involved in, the violence that day. title: WATCH: Former Trump legal adviser sought pardon after Jan. 6. House committee reveals
description: A legal adviser for former President Donald Trump, John Eastman, who had urged for Vice President Mike Pence to reject electoral votes for Joe Biden, would later ask Trump advisor Rudy Giuliani that he be given a presidential pardon in the aftermath of the Jan. 6 insurrection, Rep. Pete Aguilar, D-Calif., said during June 16 hearing by the House committee investigating the insurrection.|â€œDr. Eastman emailed Rudy Giuliani and requested he be included on a list of recipients of a presidential pardon. Dr. Eastman's email stated, 'I've decided that I should be on the pardoned list, if that is still in the works,'" Aguilar read.|Aguilar said Eastman did not receive his pardon and added that when subpoenaed by the committee to give testimony, he asserted his Fifth Amendment right against self-incrimination 100 times.|The hearing was the third of several planned by the Jan. 6 committee that focused on Trumpâ€™s efforts to pressure former Vice President Mike Pence to reject Congress' official count of Electoral College votes on the day of the attack. In the year since its creation, the committee has conducted more than 1,000 interviews, seeking critical information and documents from people witness to, or involved in, the violence that day. title: WATCH: Trump called Pence 'wimp' during heated phone call on Jan. 6, aide recalled
description: President Donald Trump placed mounting pressure on his then-vice president, Mike Pence, to overturn the results of the 2020 presidential election, the House committee investigating the Jan. 6 insurrection revealed during their June 16 hearing-- the third such public hearing they have held.|â€œTrump continued to pressure the vice president both publicly and privately,â€ Rep. Pete Aguilar, D-Calif., said during the hearing. â€œThings reached a boiling point on Jan. 6, and the consequences were disastrous.â€|The committee also played out testimony from several people who were around Trump when he called Pence on Jan. 6, who said that the tone was much different than usual and much more heated.|Nicholas Luna, former assistant to President Trump remembered Trump calling Pence a â€œwimpâ€ during that conversation. The committee also played out video testimony by Ivanka Trump, who said, â€œIt was a different tone than I had heard him take with the vice president before.â€|Aguilar and the panel want to show Trumps pressure directly contributed to the riot against the Capitol that day, and that those who breached the Capitol believed they were acting at Trumpâ€™s direction which Aguilar said put the life of his own vice president in danger.|â€œOur investigation found that early drafts of the Jan. 6 speech prepared for the president included no mention of the vice president, but the president revised it and then further ad-libbed.â€|Aguilar said after the Vice President issued his public letter, the crowd at the capitol building erupted in anger and rioters began chanting, "Hang Mike pence.â€|The hearing was the third of several planned by the Jan. 6 committee that focused on Trumpâ€™s efforts to pressure former Vice President Mike Pence to reject Congress' official count of Electoral College votes on the day of the attack. In the year since its creation, the committee has conducted more than 1,000 interviews, seeking critical information and documents from people witness to, or involved in, the violence that day. The committee postponed a hearing scheduled for June 15 that was meant to focus on Trump's efforts to replace Attorney General Bill Barr, who did not support his claims of voter fraud after the election.|Stream your PBS favorites with the PBS app: https://to.pbs.org/2Jb8twG|Find more from PBS NewsHour at https://www.pbs.org/newshour|Subscribe to our YouTube channel: https://bit.ly/2HfsCD6|Follow us:|Facebook: http://www.pbs.org/newshour|Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/newshour|Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/newshour

title: WATCH: Pence lawyer warned Trump adviser that Pence interfering in election would lead to disaster
description: Former Pence lawyer Greg Jacob testified June 16 that he had warned lawyer John Eastman the day before Jan. 6 that a plan for the vice president to reject electoral votes and send voting back to state legislatures would not survive a court challenge.|Jacob said during a hearing before the House Jan.6 committee that he told Eastman the plan he had given to former President Donald Trump in a memo violated the law.|â€œHe acknowledged it would lose 9-0 in the Supreme Court, but kept trying to say, â€˜I don't think the courts will get involved' because the issue was a 'political question,'" Jacob said.|Jacob said he believed the courts would intervene and the result would be â€œdisastrous.â€|â€œYou would have had just an unprecedented constitutional jump ball situation with that standoff, and as I expressed to him, that issue might well have to be decided in the streets,â€ Jacob said.|The hearing was the third of several planned by the Jan. 6 committee, this one focused on Trumpâ€™s efforts to pressure Vice President Mike Pence to reject Congress' official count of Electoral College votes on the day of the attack. In the year since its creation, the committee has conducted more than 1,000 interviews, seeking critical information and documents from people witness to, or involved in, the violence that day.|Stream your PBS favorites with the PBS app: https://to.pbs.org/2Jb8twG  |Find more from PBS NewsHour at https://www.pbs.org/newshour  |Subscribe to our YouTube channel: https://bit.ly/2HfsCD6  |Follow us: |TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@pbsnews  |Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/newshour|Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/newshour  |Facebook: http://www.pbs.org/newshour  |Subscribe: |PBS NewsHour podcasts: https://www.pbs.org/newshour/podcasts|Newsletters: https://www.pbs.org/newshour/subscribe

description: Former Judge J. Michael Luttig testified on June 16 as the House committee investigating the Jan. 6 attack presented its findings to the public.|Luttig told the Jan. 6 committee that if former Vice President Mike Pence carried out President Donald Trumpâ€™s demand to not count electoral votes won by President Joe Biden in the 2020 election, it would have amounted to a constitutional crisis.|â€œThat declaration of Donald Trump as the next president would have plunged America into what I believe would have been tantamount to a revolution within a constitutional crisis in America, which, in my view, â€¦ would have been the first constitutional crisis since the founding of the republic,â€ Luttig said.|The hearing was the third of several planned by the Jan. 6 committee that focused on Trumpâ€™s efforts to pressure Pence to reject Congress' official count of Electoral College votes on the day of the attack. The committee postponed a hearing scheduled for June 15 that was meant to focus on Trump's efforts to replace Attorney General Bill Barr, who did not support his claims of voter fraud after the election. |Stream your PBS favorites with the PBS app: https://to.pbs.org/2Jb8twG|Find more from PBS NewsHour at https://www.pbs.org/newshour|Subscribe to our YouTube channel: https://bit.ly/2HfsCD6|Follow us:|Facebook: http://www.pbs.org/newshour|Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/newshour|Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/newshour

title: Valerie Bertinelli's Focaccia Pizza | Valerie's Home Cooking | Food Network
description: Valerie creates a crisp and pillowy focaccia as the crust for this cheesy pizza with extra pepperoni!|Subscribe to #discoveryplus to stream more episodes of Valerie's #HomeCooking: http://discoverypl.us/2NeKVgd. |Get the recipe â–¶ https://foodtv.com/3MA6UHr|Subscribe to Food Network â–¶ http://foodtv.com/YouTube|Valerie Bertinelli is more than a successful actress. Join Valerie as she shares her passion for cooking delicious meals!|Welcome to Food Network, where learning to cook is as simple as clicking play! Grab your apron and get ready to get cookin' with some of the best chefs around the world. We'll give you a behind-the-scenes look at our best shows, take you inside our favorite restaurant and be your resource in the kitchen to make sure every meal is a 10/10!|Focaccia Pizza|RECIPE COURTESY OF VALERIE BERTINELLI|Level: Easy|Total: 3 hr|Active: 45 min|Yield: 6 servings|Ingredients|3 1/2 cups bread flour, spooned into measuring cups and then leveled off|1 1/2 teaspoons kosher salt|1 1/4 teaspoons instant yeast|1 1/2 cups lukewarm water|1 teaspoon honey|1/2 cup extra-virgin olive oil|Sauce, recipe follows|5 ounces sliced pepperoni|15 deli-style slices Monterey Jack cheese (about 8 ounces)|Dried oregano, for garnish|Red pepper flakes, for garnish|Freshly grated Parmesan, for garnish|Sauce:|One 14-ounce can crushed tomatoes|2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil|3/4 teaspoon kosher salt|1/4 teaspoon granulated sugar|1 clove garlic, finely grated|Directions|Special equipment: two 18-by-13-inch rimmed baking sheets|Add the flour, salt and yeast to the bowl of a stand mixer and whisk to combine. Add the water, honey and 3 tablespoons of the olive oil to a 2-cup measuring cup. Whisk to combine. Add the water mixture to the mixer bowl and use a rubber spatula to incorporate the ingredients slightly. Attach the bowl to the stand mixer fitted with the dough hook and mix on low speed until the mixture forms into a ball and no loose flour is left at the base of the bowl, 3 to 4 minutes. Turn the mixer up to medium speed and knead for 2 to 3 minutes.|Pour the remaining olive oil into a 18-by-13-inch rimmed baking sheet. Turn the dough out onto the baking sheet. Turn it once to coat all the sides of the dough in the olive oil. Cover the pan with an inverted baking sheet of the same size and leave in a warm place to rise until doubled in size, about 2 hours.|After 2 hours, preheat the oven to 500 degrees F.|Remove the top baking sheet and, using the tips of your fingers, delicately stretch the dough until it almost reaches the edges of the pan. Cover again with the rimmed baking sheet and let the dough rest while you make the Sauce (see recipe below).|Uncover the dough and delicately stretch the dough to reach all the edges of the pan again. If the dough springs back too much, let the dough sit for another 5 to 10 minutes before trying to stretch it further. Once the dough is stretched to fit the pan, top it with the sauce. Cover the sauce completely with the pepperoni, then top the pepperoni with the sliced cheese. Transfer the pizza to the oven and bake until the cheese is lightly browned in spots and the crust is golden, 15 to 20 minutes.|Remove the pizza from the oven and use a large spatula to transfer it to a cutting board. Top with dried oregano, red pepper flakes and Parmesan. Cut into 16 squares and serve immediately.|Sauce:|Yield: About 1 cup|Add the tomatoes, olive oil, salt, sugar and garlic to a mixing bowl. title: How Flying Scenes Are Shot For Movies And TV | Movies Insider | Insider
description: One of the biggest challenges for Hollywoodâ€™s stunt performers is creating flight that is both safe and believable. Since George Reeves portrayed Superman in the 1950s, movies and TV shows have used an endless variety of wires, pans, and other rigs to lift actors up high. The best tools depend on the type of flying on-screen. A huge breakthrough came in 1978's â€œSupermanâ€ when a visual effects artist discovered a way to operate the camera so that Christopher Reeve would appear to be flying even when he was lying flat. title: European leaders visit Kyiv in show of solidarity with Ukraine - BBC News
description: German Chancellor Olaf Scholz, French President Emmanuel Macron, Italian Prime Minister Mario Draghi and Romanian President Klaus Iohannis have met with Ukrainian President Zelensky in Kyiv.|The French, German and Italian leaders took an overnight train from Poland and were joined by the Romanian leader in Ukraine to meet with Zelensky, where they hope to counter criticisms of their support for the country and offer help to its people.|Their visit has been met with scorn by Russia, with Kremlin spokesperson Dmitry Peskov saying he hoped it would not focus solely on supplying Ukraine with weapons as that would cause further damage to the country.|Former Russian president Dmitry Medvedev says there is "zero use" in the leaders being there.|Please subscribe HERE http://bit.ly/1rbfUog|#Russia #Ukraine #BBCNewsPlease subscribe HERE http://bit.ly/1rbfUog|#BBCNews

title: Easy Oatmeal Cookies (No Eggs)
description: These oatmeal cookies are so easy to make, that you can prepare them even with your kids. These cookies are eggless, dairy free and basically VEGAN! And as a bonus you can add to them any additions that you like, such as; nuts, dried fruits and more. So, if you are looking for an easy cookie recipe, this recipe is the easiest and tastiest you can find. |â–ºFull written recipe: https://www.thecookingfoodie.com/recipe/Easy-Oatmeal-Cookies-Recipe-No-Eggs|â–º Equipment I used in this video: https://www.amazon.com/shop/thecookingfoodie|â–ºMore Recipes You Might Like:|Easy Banana Oatmeal Cookies: https://youtu.be/U7sWA5fU0NU|Microwave Cheesecake: https://youtu.be/37GhHFd2mRM|7 Easy Desserts Anyone Can Make: https://youtu.be/Wh-Lojh1vbI|Healthy Banana Oatmeal Pancakes: https://youtu.be/yoygW728p14|Healthy Gluten Free Banana Bread Recipe: https://youtu.be/u7urpX7VEjM|â–ºFOLLOW ME:|Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/thecookingfoodie/ |Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/thecookingfoodie |Website: https://www.thecookingfoodie.com/|Makes about 16-19 cookies|Ingredients:|3/4 cup + 1 tablespoon (100g) Flour|1 cup (90g) Quick Oats|1/4 teaspoon Salt|1 teaspoon Baking powder |1/2 teaspoon cinnamon (optional) |1/4 cup (60g) Applesauce |1/4 cup (50g) Sugar|1 teaspoon Vanilla extract|1/3 cup (80ml) Vegetable oil/Coconut oil|1/4 cup Dried cranberries|1/4 cup Nuts of your choice |Directions:|1. Preheat oven to 350F (180C), line baking tray with parchment paper and set aside.|2. In a large bowl whisk all dry ingredients: flour, oats, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Set aside.|3. In a separate bowl, whisk applesauce, oil, vanilla extract and sugar. Whisk until combined.|4. Add flour mixture to the wet mixture, then add chopped nuts, cranberries and mix until dough is formed.|5. Shape the batter into small balls and arrange them onto the baking tray. Slightly flatten.|6. Bake for 12-14, until golden.|7. Allow to cool for 5-10 minutes.

title: The Ready Room | Why Nurse Chapel Sees Spock As More Than A "Hot Snack" | Paramount+
description: This week, actress Jess Bush (Nurse Christine Chapel) joins host Wil Wheaton (Star Trek: The Next Generation) in The Ready Room to discuss Episode 7 of Star Trek: Strange New Worlds, "The Serene Squall." title: Larry June: Tiny Desk (Home) Concert
description: This year, NPR Music is celebrating Black Music Month with an array of brand new Tiny Desk concerts â€” both from home and from behind our beloved Desk. Together, these artists represent the past, present and future of Black music. This month of carefully curated shows is a celebration of Black artists expressing themselves in ways we've never seen before, and of the Tiny Desk's unique way of showcasing that talent.|Bobby Carter | June 16, 2022|Larry June is the indie-rap hustle personified. His graduation from the streets has made way for his true purpose in rhyme: healthy living. The organic fruits and juices on the table in this performance indicate the lifestyle fervently pushed in his music. The two cell phones sitting beside him remind us that business is booming. He starts with a few signature adlibs before imploring, "Don't check me / Check the air quality." This lavish living room setting, with the Los Angeles night sky as a backdrop, sets the proper mood for Larry June's Tiny Desk (home) concert.|The Bay Area emcee has been at this for a while, adopting the independent approach like many before him: saturating the market with product and profiting from shows and merch. While much of the music industry stumbled and stalled during the uncertainty of 2020, Larry put up numbers, releasing half a dozen projects from his home studio. Here, he's able to comfortably sit back in the laid-back tone we're used to hearing on his records and not the dialed-up mood of his stage show. His band, The NME, replays and beefs up the sample on 2020's "Just me & you," plus songs from 2019's Out The Trunk and Early Bird.|In theory, a motivational rapper rapping about bike rides, hikes and investments would be deemed shtick in 2022 â€” yet he's here, authentic and refreshing. Good job, Larry.|SET LIST|"SLS 30 Days"|"Just me & you"|"Dear, Snow"|"Let's Drive To Vegas"|MUSICIANS|Larry June: vocals|Isaac Oshuntola: bass|Eddie Hamilton: guitar|Jarrett Freeman: keys|Jack Monk: guitar|Brandon Stennett: drums |CREDITS|Producer: Marco Alexander, Andrew Min|Video Assistant: Kian Wang |Recording Engineer: Migui Maloles |Assistant Recording Engineer: Joshua "Jay Que" Queen |Mixed by: Migui Maloles, Todd Cooper |TINY DESK TEAM|Producer: Bobby Carter|Video Producer: Michael Zamora|Audio Mastering: Josh Rogosin|Animation: Kaz Fantone|Tiny Production Team: Bob Boilen, Kara Frame, Joshua Bryant, Maia Stern, Ashley Pointer|VP, Visuals and Music: Keith Jenkins|Senior VP, Programming: Anya Grundmann|#NPRMusic #TinyDesk #LarryJune

title: SriLankan Airlines pilot averts mid-air mishap; Disobeys order to climb 35,000 feet. Saves 600 lives
description: SriLankan Airlines pilot refused to follow ATC command but is being applauded. The Srilankan flight had been told to climb to 35,000 feet from the 33,000 feet they were flying at. Right then, the Srilankan flight detected a British Airways flight just 15 miles away from them flying at 35,000 feet. The Srilankan pilots refused to climb despite being cleared twice erroneously by the Ankara air traffic control. Minutes later, the air traffic responded urgently, informing the Srilankan flight not to climb as there was already a flight right above at 35,000 feet. However, the vigilant pilot had not obeyed the ATC despite repeated requests. With his alertness he saved over 600 lives by averting a major mid-air collision. Watch this report to know more.|#srilankanairlines #flysrilankan #srilankanpilot #lankanpilot #midair #midairscare #britishairways #atc #airtraffic #airtravel

title: Naura Ayu - Menikmati Sedih | Official Music Video
description: Naura Ayu - Menikmati Sedih | Official Music Video|Semua orang pasti pernah merasakan kesedihan, dan rasa itu sebaiknya diterima dengan lapang dan dinikmati, bukan ditampik atau disangkal. Lewat single terbarunya yang berjudul â€œMenikmati Sedihâ€, Naura Ayu menjelaskan bahwa kesedihan patut disyukuri karena pada akhirnya, dapat memberikan kebahagiaan yang kita butuhkan.|â€œMenikmati Sedihâ€ adalah kisah personal Naura Ayu. Luapan isi hatinya sekaligus penenang untuk jiwanya. Meski sedih, banyak pesan tersirat dan makna akan kebahagiaan di dalamnya.|â€œSecara umum, â€œMenikmati Sedihâ€ adalah cara aku healing dari sebuah kesedihan. Inspirasinya dari aku sendiri dan juga karena aku tahu semua orang pasti pernah merasakan rasa ini,â€ ucap Naura Ayu.|Naura Ayu pun menjalani workshop dengan Barsena Bestandhi, A&R Trinity Optima Production, di rumahnya. Kala itu, banyak quotes dan kalimat yang membuatnya terinspirasi untuk memperindah lagu â€œMenikmati Sedihâ€. Terkait rekaman, Naura Ayu mengaku lagu barunya ini cukup menantang karena dari sisi vokal, range-nya cukup lebar dan banyak hal baru lain di dalamnya.|Soal video klip, kamar tidur menjadi konsep utama. Alasannya, karena kamar tidur merupakan tempat utama dan ternyaman bagi banyak orang untuk merasakan kesedihan. Ada juga hal-hal lainnya seperti kehadiran liontin yang dia pakai.|â€œLiontin itu yang melambangkan rasa kesedihan aku. Aku menyimpan air mataku di sana. Pesannya seperti, setelah kita menikmati kesedihan, kita bisa menemukan kebahagian dan mensyukurinya,â€ ujar Naura Ayu.|Naura Ayu berharap, â€œMenikmati Sedihâ€ disukai oleh para pendengarnya dan memotivasi sekaligus membantu orang-orang yang sedang mengalami kesedihan.|â€œTerima kasih banyak atas apresiasinya dan terima kasih sudah meluangkan waktu untuk mendengarkan â€œMenikmati Sedihâ€. Semoga teman-teman yang sedang berada di situasi sedih bisa menemukan cara menikmati sedihnya masing-masing dan berani menghadapinya. An easy and simple flavoured gravy-based curry recipe prepared with black chickpeas and assorted dry spices. It is one of the popular north Indian curry recipes shared with a wide range of Indian flatbreads and particularly shared with poori & bhatura. There are myriad ways of preparing this curry, but this post describes the popular Punjabi Dhaba style channa masala gravy recipe.|Kala Chana Recipe | Black Chickpea Curry | Kala Channa Masala Curry with step-by-step photo and video recipe. Indian curry recipes are versatile and with the same onion and tomato-based gravy, there could be myriad flavoured curries. The most famous vegetarian curries are typically crowded with paneer cubes due to their rich creaminess and sweet taste. However, the same gravy curry base can also be used with other types of hero ingredients and Black chickpeas are one such popular street-style curry recipe.|#hebbarskitchen

title: The TASTIEST KFC in the WORLD!! KFC Zinger Sandwich & KFC Original Chicken in Trinidad and Tobago!!
description: ğŸ‡¹ğŸ‡¹KFC TRINIDAD: https://www.instagram.com/kfc.tt |ğŸŒ MY TRAVEL/FOOD BLOG: https://davidsbeenhere.com/ |After arriving back in Port of Spain to finish my epic trip through Trinidad and Tobago, I did something Iâ€™d been told I needed to do from the very beginningâ€¦eat some KFC! Come with me as I experience Trinidadian fried chicken at KFC in Port of Spain, Trinidad!|KFC in Trinidad was ranked the tastiest KFC on Earth, so I was excited to try it out! There are 16 locations in total on the island. There, I met their marketing manager, Jillian, who would let me try their famous chicken!|âš½ï¸BOL: https://www.instagram.com/bol.football  |ğŸ‘• DAVIDâ€™S BEEN HERE MERCH: https://teespring.com/stores/davids-been-here |Inside, it looks like a typical KFC, but they do something different here: all of their chicken is fresh, never frozen. Itâ€™s brought in fresh every day!| KFC uses 11 special herbs and spices in their original recipe. In the kitchen, I watched them flour and fry some original chicken. It fries in the pressure fryer for 16 minutes and itâ€™s ready to go! |Then, I saw them make some spicy breading mix with 25 pounds of flour and their spice mixture. The flour looks more yellow once the spices are completely incorporated. Then, they add the chicken to it!|They have making the chicken down to a science! Depending on what you order, itâ€™s cooked for a certain number of minutes and dredged a certain number of times. That way, no matter what you order, it comes out perfect every time!|We got an order of their original recipe, as well as the hot and spicy, which is what the KFC in Trinidad is known for. The original with 11 herbs and spices was juicy and crispy. I loved the crispiness of the batter. Itâ€™s the same recipe everywhere!|I had some pepper sauce with it, which was glazy and hot, but not unbearable.|Then, we jumped on the hot & spicy, which also had a doable level of spice. The pepper sauce was hotter, for sure. It was a spicier version of the original!|Then, Jillian mixed together some ketchup, mustard, and pepper sauce, which was amazing together with the chicken. What a combination of sweetness and heat! The ketchup was different from the ketchup in the U.S. It was sweeter!|Next, we got some fries, corn on the cob, buttermilk biscuits, and Trini coleslaw. I started with the biscuit, which was brown and crispy on the outside and fluffy in the middle. They finished it with some butter! |The fries were perfectly salted and crispy. They were fantastic in the sauce mixture. Then, I tried some of the Trini coleslaw on the biscuit. I loved the hot biscuit with the cold and crunchy coleslaw. It wasnâ€™t too wet or too dry.|The corn on the cob was super buttery and very tasty. It was delicious!|Next, they brought us the Zinger, a chicken sandwich made with a spicy fried white meat filet, mayo, and lettuce. I liked that it didnâ€™t have tomato on it, which makes the sandwich soggy. I liked adding more coleslaw onto it!|The Zinger was developed in Trinidad and Tobago in 1984, and itâ€™s now available in over 100 KFCs around the world! I loved the light amount of mayo and lettuce. Adding the pepper sauce was amazing, too!|Then, Jillian gave me a KFC Carnival sweatshirt with a bucket with a steel pan on top. |Finally, we finished with a scorching hot sweet apple pie! It was straight out of the fryer, but was flaky with a gooey interior.|Where have you been?|Subscribe Here! http://bit.ly/DavidsbeenhereSub|Top videos! http://bit.ly/DavidsbeenhereTopVideos|Follow Me:|+ INSTAGRAM â–º https://instagram.com/davidsbeenhere  |+ FACEBOOK â–º https://www.facebook.com/davidsbeenhere  |+ TWITTER â–º https://twitter.com/davidsbeenhere |+ MY BLOG! â–º http://davidsbeenhere.com/ |Contact Me:|+BUSINESS EMAIL â–º david@godandbeauty.com|#Davidsbeenhere #TrinidadAndTobago #PortOfSpain #TrinidadianFood #DavidinTrinidad|About Me:|My name is David Hoffmann. Since starting Davidâ€™s Been Here in 2008, I have traveled to over 1,300 destinations in 88 countries to experience and document unique cultures on my YouTube channel, travel blog, and social media.| |I highlight culture and historical sites, but my passion is food! I love to experience and showcase the different flavors each destination has to offer, from casual street food to gourmet restaurant dining.|Where have you been?| |P.S. Thank you for watching my videos and subscribing!

This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Shailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi / Raj Anadkat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. title: European leaders Scholz, Macron and Draghi arrive in Kyiv to meet with Ukraine's Zelenskyy | DW News
description: German Chancellor Olaf Scholz, French President Emmanuel Macron and Italian Prime Minister Mario Draghi arrived in Kyiv on Thursday, the French presidential palace said. Scholz said the three leaders wanted "to show their support for Ukraine and the citizens of Ukraine." "But we don't just want to demonstrate solidarity, we also want to assure that the help we organize â€” financial and humanitarian, but also when it comes to weapons â€” will be continued," he said. Support will continue for as long as is necessary, he said. The trio took an overnight train to Kyiv from Poland. They are expected to meet with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy. Major German and Italian media outlets, including Germany's ZDF and Italy's Repubblica, had earlier published a photo of the three leaders on the train. Key to the overall design was to connect the attic storage, previously only accessible by a common exterior staircase, to the rest of the apartment by way of an internal staircase and changing the storage into the bedroom. The internal staircase is housed inside a central floor-to-ceiling oak veneer storage wall, which also extends into the bedroom forming the balustrade with integrated shelves. The storage wall consists of plenty of closed as well as open storage spaces on the edges, accessible from multiple sides. The new kitchen was shifted out to the open space which includes a combined dining room, freeing up space to transform the old kitchen space into an office. description: The official audio for David Bowie - Starman (Top Of The Pops Version - 2022 Mix)|Celebrating 50 years of 'The Rise and Fall of Ziggy Stardust and the Spiders From Mars', this new version of STARMAN takes the backing track (recorded at Trident Studios on 29th June) and backing vocals, featuring a one-off Bowie ad-lib, recorded for the show and adds the lead vocals from the album version (recorded at Trident Studios on 4th February). Creating and discarding a variety of personae and restlessly challenging musical boundaries, Bowie released timeless albums including Space Oddity, Hunky Dory, The Rise and Fall of Ziggy Stardustâ€¦, Aladdin Sane, Diamond Dogs, Young Americans, Station to Station, "Heroes,â€ Let's Dance, Heathen, The Next Day and many more. Blackstar, Bowieâ€™s 28th and final studio album, was released on his 69th birthday, January 8, 2016. David Bowie died on January 10, 2016, two days after the release of Blackstar. His body of work, his influence on the worlds of music, art, fashion, film, theatre and beyond, and his legacy of innovation and reinvention will live forever. 2022 kicks off with Bowie at 75, a celebration of his 75th birthday with the Brilliant Adventure box set, the previously unreleased Toy, the 50th anniversary of Ziggy Stardust and a series of special events.|#DavidBowie #Starman #ZiggyStardust #ZiggyStardust50 #Bowie

description: Listen to Soruthihudu Maniya Maligi on all audio streaming platforms: https://allok.bfan.link/soruthihudu-maniya-maligi|Spotify: https://allok.bfan.link/soruthihudu-maniya-maligi/spotify|Apple Music: https://allok.bfan.link/soruthihudu-maniya-maligi/appleMusic|Youtube Music: https://allok.bfan.link/soruthihudu-maniya-maligi/youtubeMusic|Amazon music: https://allok.bfan.link/soruthihudu-maniya-maligi/amazonMusic|Jio Saavn: https://allok.bfan.link/soruthihudu-maniya-maligi/jiosaavn|Gaana: https://allok.bfan.link/soruthihudu-maniya-maligi/gaana|Resso: https://allok.bfan.link/soruthihudu-maniya-maligi/resso|Credits:|Song: Soruthihudu Maniya Maligi|INSPIRED FROM ORIGINAL SORUTIHUDU MANIYA MALIGI WRITTEN BY: SHISHUNAALA SHARIFA|MUSIC COMPOSED, RAP LYRICS, PRODUCED & PERFORMED: ALL OK |CONCEPT/DI: ELEVEN ELEMENTS|DIRECTOR/DOP: RAJARAM RAJENDRAN|MUSIC ARRANGEMENT & PRODUCTION: GAGAN BADERIYA & ALL OK|EDITOR & VFX - JYOLSNA PANICKER |MIXING & MASTERING: ANIKET MOHANTY |AERIAL PHOTOGRAPHY: SANDEEP ROY|CONTUME DESIGN & STYLING: HARINI RAMAKRISHNA |FLUTE LIVE RECCORDING BHARDY FLUTER|PRODUCTION MANAGER ARJUN SUBRAMANYA|ADDITIONAL PROGRAMMING : NESZ |POSTER DESIGNER ASHWIN RAMESH|Team Believe Artist Services: https://www.instagram.com/believeasd/|Soruthihudu Maniya Maligi is a famous folk song that has been reimagined by All OK in a unique way, giving it more soul and infusing an electronica vibe to it, along with new age rap verse. Sorutihudu is a philosophical song about human ignorance and how to attain wisdom and clarity in order to make our existence meaningful, happy and fulfilling in all spheres of life. This philosophy is explained through a beautiful analogy of a leaking roof in a heavy night storm; where water dripping inside the house is caused because of a gap in our understanding and acceptance due to ego, greed and ignorance. But the song offers a simple solution to get out of this state for a soul awakening, that can lead to a better future through inner work. All these intense emotions have been conveyed though a brilliant rap and driving beats that will engage audience of all age-groups, young and old. |(The original song was part of a Kannada biographical drama called Santha Shishunala Shariefaru, written in 1990)|Follow All Ok on:|Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/all_ok_official/|TikTok: https://vm.tiktok.com/C8JbYs/|Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/iamallok|Sharechat: https://sharechat.com/profile/yaakinge|Twitter: https://twitter.com/allok02|Don't forget to subscribe to the official YouTube channel of All Ok:|https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCUwSeY7lUdZSP0vuflq1oPA|For Licensing enquiries: |Email:- sync-india@believedigital.com|For booking enquiries:|artistbooking-india@believedigital.com|#allok #SoruthihuduManiyaMaligi

title: Hadi Tjahjanto Janji Sikat Mafia Tanah
description: JAKARTA, KOMPAS.TV  Mantan Panglima TNI Marsekal Hadi Tjahjanto kini resmi menjabat Menteri ATR/BPN gantikan Sofyan Djalil.||||Usai acara serah terima jabatan, kepada media Hadi pun membeberkan 3 poin fokus kerjanya di 100 hari pertama. ||||Ia berjanji mengatasi persoalan di Kementerian ATR/BPN dengan cara terjun langsung ke lapangan salah satunya terkait masalah mafia tanah.||||"Oleh sebab itu saya sampaikan tadi adalah saya sama dengan Pak Sofyan Djalil akan turun ke lapangan, permasalahan di lapangan akan terus kita eliminir supaya mereka juga tidak menemui permasalahan. Kita akan tekan, dan saya akan ke lapangan akan melihat secara langsung dan akan menanyakan kepada mereka. Tidak hanya laporan saja tapi saya akan menanyakan masyarakat, apakah masih ada masalah mafia tanah,"ujar Hadi Tjahjanto, Rabu (15/6/2022). ||||Baca Juga Jokowi Buka-bukaan Alasan Lantik Hadi Tjahjanto dan Zulhas jadi Menteri di https://www.kompas.tv/article/299437/jokowi-buka-bukaan-alasan-lantik-hadi-tjahjanto-dan-zulhas-jadi-menteri||||Hal lain yang akan ia tanyakan ke masyarakat juga masih terkait konflik kepemilikan tanah, besarnya harga sewa, hingga permasalahan-permasalahan pendapatan negara bukan pajak yang terlalu besar. ||||"Ya tadi kita bicara juga, minggu depan saya akan turun ke lapangan untuk bisa mengidentifikasi permasalahan itu ya. Yang penting saya akan ke lapangan saya akan kelapangan. Masyarakat bisa menyampaikan ke saya."lanjutnya. ||||Video Editor: Agung|| ||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/299550/hadi-tjahjanto-janji-sikat-mafia-tanah

title: PTDI Serah Terima Pesawat CN235-220 ke Menhan, Prabowo: Untuk Patroli Maritim TNI AL
description: KOMPAS.TV - Direktur Utama PT Dirgantara Indonesia, Gita Amperiawan menyerahkan langsung 1 unit pesawat CN 235-220 dan 2 unit helikopter antikapal selam kepada Menteri Pertahanan RI, Prabowo Subianto.||||Serah terima ini adalah kerja sama antara Kementerian Pertahanan dan PT Dirgantara Indonesia.||||Pesawat CN 235-220 nantinya digunakan TNI Angkatan Laut untuk patroli maritim, mengamankan perairan Indonesia.||||Prabowo menyebutkan, PT Dirgantara Indonesia harus mampu memproduksi pesawat CN 235 sebanyak 20 unit dalam 5 tahun juga pesawat tempur, dan ini tugas berat bagi PTDI. ||||Baca Juga Persepi Nilai Politik Transaksional di Pemilu 2024 Masih Ada, Ini Faktornya di https://www.kompas.tv/article/299555/persepi-nilai-politik-transaksional-di-pemilu-2024-masih-ada-ini-faktornya|||||| ||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/299560/ptdi-serah-terima-pesawat-cn235-220-ke-menhan-prabowo-untuk-patroli-maritim-tni-al

title: Zulkifli Mendag Baru Sidak Pasar, Syok Semua Ngeluh Harga Naik
description: JAKARTA, KOMPAS.TV  Mendag Zulkifli Hasan yang baru dilantik kemarin, pada Kamis (16/6/2022) pagi telah sidak pasar Cibubur untuk mengecek sejumlah harga kebutuhan pokok. ||||Pada sidaknya ini, Zulkifli mengaku kaget banyak keluhan dari pedagang dan pembeli terkait harga-harga yang serba naik. ||||"Kita lihat harga-harga. Terus terang saya syok. Pembelinya ngeluh yang dagang juga ngeluh. Terasa sekali memang beban hidup itu meningkat. Dan itu kita tadi lihat langsung. Akibat harga-harga kebutuhan pokok naik kecuali beras. Cabai naik 20-30 persen dari 80 ribu cabe rawit antara Rp 80-110 ribu. Bawang merah naik 20 persen. Telur Rp 26 ribu sekarang Rp 29 ribu per kilo,"ucap Zulkifli menjabarkan pantauan harga di pasar. ||||Baca Juga Zulkifli Hasan Buka Suara Usai Dilantik Sebagai Mendag, Permasalahan Minyak Goreng Akan Dituntaskan di https://www.kompas.tv/article/299328/zulkifli-hasan-buka-suara-usai-dilantik-sebagai-mendag-permasalahan-minyak-goreng-akan-dituntaskan||||Ia pun berjanji akan menuntaskan persoalan harga ini dengan berkoordinasi dengan kementerian terkait seperti Menko dan Mentan. ||||Kemudian terkait minyak, Mendag Zulkifli juga meminta pelaku usaha mendengarkan jeritan emak-emak. ||||"Tapi jangka pendek pelaku usaha besar migor, udah untung banyak. Harus ada asas keadilan. Jangan mengejar untung besar, dari kebun, minyak, itu kan luar biasa. Kita minta dengarkan suara rakyat, suara emak-emak. Migor 14 ribu tidak tawar-tawar mesti tersedia. Saya akan sekuat daya upaya segala peraturan yang ada,"jelasnya. ||||Video Editor: Agung|| ||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/299575/zulkifli-mendag-baru-sidak-pasar-syok-semua-ngeluh-harga-naik

title: Momen Jokowi Makan Siang Bareng Ketum Parpol Koalisi, Berikut Nama-Nama Ketum yang Diundang
description: JAKARTA, KOMPAS.TV - Jelang acara pelantikan menteri baru di Kabinet Indonesia Maju, Presiden Joko Widodo menjamu makan siang Ketua Umum partai pendukung pemerintah di Istana Negara.||||Tampak Presiden Joko Widodo berbincang santai dengan Ketua Umum PDI Perjuangan, Megawati Soekarnoputri.||||Hadir pula dalam jamuan ini, Ketua Umum Partai Golkar Airlangga Hartarto, Ketua Umum Partai Nasdem Surya Paloh, Ketua Umum Gerindra Prabowo Subianto, Ketua Umum PKB Muhaimin Iskandar, Ketua Umum PPP Suharso Monoarfa, dan Ketua Umum PAN Zulkifli Hasan.||||Selain itu, kehangatan antara Presiden Joko Widodo dan Ketua Umum PDI-P Megawati juga kembali terlihat.||||Jokowi dan Mega terlihat berjalan bersama saat memasuki ruangan sebelum acara pelantikan.||||Baca Juga Persepi Nilai Politik Transaksional di Pemilu 2024 Masih Ada, Ini Faktornya di https://www.kompas.tv/article/299555/persepi-nilai-politik-transaksional-di-pemilu-2024-masih-ada-ini-faktornya|||||| ||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/299558/momen-jokowi-makan-siang-bareng-ketum-parpol-koalisi-berikut-nama-nama-ketum-yang-diundang

The Pioneer Woman is an open invitation into Ree Drummond's life: The award-winning blogger and best-selling cookbook author comes to Food Network and shares her special brand of home cooking, from throw-together suppers to elegant celebrations. The series, set against the incredible story of life at home on the range, is the next best thing to actually sitting on a stool in Ree's kitchen.|Welcome to Food Network, where learning to cook is as simple as clicking play! Grab your apron and get ready to get cookin' with some of the best chefs around the world. We'll give you a behind-the-scenes look at our best shows, take you inside our favorite restaurant and be your resource in the kitchen to make sure every meal is a 10/10!|Chicken Apricot Panini|RECIPE COURTESY OF REE DRUMMOND|Level: Easy|Total: 9 hr 5 min (includes marinating time)|Active: 1 hr 5 min|Yield: 1 panini|Ingredients|2 tablespoons apricot preserves|2 tablespoons mayonnaise |1 piece Perfect Grilled Chicken (thawed if frozen), recipe follows|2 slices good, thick sourdough bread|2 slices provolone cheese |4 fresh sage leaves |1/4 red onion, sliced very thin |2 tablespoons butter, softened|Perfect Grilled Chicken|2 cups olive oil|6 tablespoons honey|3 heaping tablespoons Dijon mustard|1 tablespoon salt|2 teaspoons ground thyme|2 teaspoons ground oregano|Juice of 12 lemons|24 boneless, skinless chicken breasts|Directions|Special equipment: a panini maker, optional|In a small bowl, add the apricot preserves and mayonnaise and stir to combine. Slice the Perfect Grilled Chicken into strips.|To build the sandwich, spread both slices of bread with the apricot-mayonnaise spread. On one half, lay a slice of cheese, the chicken strips, sage, red onion slices and the second slice of cheese. Put on the top piece of bread and spread softened butter on both sides of the sandwich.|Grill the sandwich in a hot panini maker until golden and crisp. (If you do not have a panini maker, you can grill the sandwich in a skillet, laying another heavy skillet on top of the sandwich to press it together. Turn to grill the other side in the same way.)|Perfect Grilled Chicken:|Yield: 24 servings.|Mix together the olive oil, honey, mustard, salt, thyme, oregano and lemon juice in a large shallow container.|Pound the chicken breasts to uniform thickness and add them to the marinade. Flip and cook until golden brown on the other side and cooked all the way through, another 4 to 5 minutes. title: EXCLUSIVE Interview with Minkah Fitzpatrick after signing a new five-year deal | Pittsburgh Steelers
description: Minkah Fitzpatrick talks about signing a new five-year contract with the Pittsburgh Steelers, who he is as a player, the team's defense, and more.|On Wednesday, the Steelers signed two-time All-Pro safety Minkah Fitzpatrick to a new five-year contract. The financial terms of the deal were not released by the team.|Fitzpatrick has been a mainstay for the Steelers defense since he was acquired via a trade with the Miami Dolphins following Week 2 of the 2019 NFL season. During his time with the Steelers, he has twice been selected Associated Press First-Team All-Pro (2019, 2020) and was voted to the Pro Bowl in both of those seasons.|He has started all 46 games he has played in for the Steelers, missing just one game in 2021. For his career he has started 59 of the 64 games he played in.|Fitzpatrick has amassed 350 tackles, 237 of them solo stops, 36 passes defensed, 13 interceptions, including three returned for a touchdown, eight sacks, five tackles for a loss, five fumble recoveries and four forced fumbles in his first four seasons in the NFL.|In 2021 Fitzpatrick had his first 100 tackle season when he recorded 124 tackles to lead the Steelers, 84 of them solo stops, along with two interceptions, nine passes defensed, one forced fumble and one fumble recovery.|His career-high 124 tackles led all defensive backs in the NFL last season and were tied for the fifth-most by a defensive back in a single season since 2016 and most by a Steelers defensive back since 1987.|In 2020 Fitzpatrick led the Steelers in tackles with 79, and added 11 passes defensed, four interceptions, including one returned for a touchdown against Cleveland in Week 6, one tackle for a loss, one forced fumble and a fumble recovery. He finished the season tied for seventh in the NFL in interceptions. He was rewarded for his efforts with his selection to the AP All-Pro team and the Pro Bowl.|During the 2019 season, which included 14 games in Pittsburgh and two in Miami, Fitzpatrick had five interceptions, all with the Steelers, two forced fumbles and two fumble recoveries, while coming in and making a huge impact on the defense. Fitzpatrick recorded defensive touchdowns in back-to-back games. In his rookie season he played in 16 games, starting 11. He had 79 tackles, 50 of them solo stops, two interceptions, and nine passes defensed. Fitzpatrick picked off Kirk Cousins against Minnesota and returned it 50 yards for a touchdown. In his time in Miami, Fitzpatrick had 90 tackles, two interceptions, including one returned for a touchdown, one forced fumble, and one fumble recovery.|A three-year starter at Alabama, he played in 42 games, starting 38. He had 171 tackles, including 109 solo stops, four and a half sacks, nine interceptions, 35 pass defenses and two forced fumbles. He won the Jim Thorpe Award as the nation's top defensive back his final season and became the third player in NCAA history to win both the Chuck Bednarik and Jim Thorpe Awards, joining Charles Woodson and Patrick Peterson with that honor. title: Federal Reserve implements highest interest rate hike in decades to combat inflation
description: The Federal Reserve on Wednesday ramped up its efforts to fight inflation with a notable interest rate hike. Officials voted to raise rates by three-quarters of a point, a jump higher than expected just a week ago. Fed chair Jerome Powell acknowledged the ongoing rate hikes might slow growth later this year, as the Fed projected unemployment would rise to 4 percent by 2024. title: Avatar: The Last Airbender Is Coming Back in a Big Way - IGN The Fix: Entertainment
description: There's three new Avatar: The Last Airbender movies in development at Paramount and Nickelodeon Animation. The upcoming animation projects were announced at the Annecy International Film Festival, where it was revealed that several #Avatar and The Legend of Korra veterans would be returning to work on the projects, including the co-creators Brian Konietzko and Michael DiMartino. This is just the beginning of the expansive Avatar Airbender and #LegendOfKorra universe Nickelodeon is setting out to create, which will encompass multiple TV shows and movies across a variety of platforms. In other news, Samuel L. Jackson is content with his current roles in Hollywood and tired of chasing roles that might win him an Oscar. And finally in entertainment news, we have our first look at Ryan Gosling as Ken in the Barbie movie.|#IGN #Avatar

title: Obi-Wan Kenobi EPISODE 5 BREAKDOWN YES FINALLY!
description: For me, this episode was a massive win. It portrayed Vader exactly how he should be, and how he is in the games and comics. It showed the beautiful training with Anakin and Obi-Wan and tied it into how each of them felt later on now in present day. It was magnificent. I really enjoyed this episode.|we start this episode off on coruscant, where anakin and obi wan are training together.|I loved how Kenobi tells them Vader is coming and he wonâ€™t stop for pleasantries or to be patient, when they ask how does he know, we get a flashback of Anakin and Obi-Wanâ€™s fighting continued. This is amazing as it shows the lessons Obi-Wan was teaching Anakin which could have saved his life in their duel had he actually listened to them. Kenobi tells him that he grows too aggressive, a jediâ€™s goal is to defend life, not take it. This really shows some red flags with anakin and it does so perfectly. Portraying Anakin as the aggressor, which falls perfectly in line with his style of fighting, form 5 djem so, the offensive form. Whereas Obi-wanâ€™s is soresu, form 3.|He realizes that the only way Reva can know that Vader is Anakin is if she was a youngling at the Jedi temple during order 66. He tells her Anakin killed younglings, and she has a flashback. She tells him that the younglings thought he was there to help them and that she hid with the bodies of her youngling friends. Kenobi realizes she isnâ€™t serving Vader, but rather hunting him, to get closer to him. The rank of Grand Inquisitor grants the GI to be closer to Vader on dangerous missions, meaning more chances for Reva to fight or blind side Vader. Her anger with Kenobi is revealed as we learn she hates him to failing Anakin, and causing him to execute Order 66 on the Jedi. Blaming Obi-Wan for what happened to the galaxy and her friends.|Kenobi realizes heâ€™s beaten, as we get another flashback of Anakin getting the upper hand on Obi-Wan. He strikes down on Obi-Wan who is cornered and defending himself down on a knee. This same angle mimics Luke attacking Vader in the same way in Return of the Jedi. the only difference is Anakin keeps attacking whereas Luke stops himself. Showing the difference between father and son. I also want to note that this choreography is very similar if not identical to their duel on Mustafar as they go through the tight walls into the control room. |The flashback shows Anakin using his iconic behind the back move as he moves as swiftly as he did. Hayden doesnâ€™t miss a beat after 17 years and continues to be a great swordsman with Ewan. He disarms obi-wan and learns a powerful lesson foreshadowing his loss on Mustafar.|As they ready to leave, Vader breaks through the doors and sees the ship taking off as he controls it with the force. This scene was the most badass scene Iâ€™ve seen with Disneyâ€™s Star Wars. This was straight out of force unleashed where starkiller was controlling the star destroyer, it echoed a lot of that scene. As he drops the ship down, he tears it apart with the powers of the dark side only to see the emergency shuttle escape and blast off into space, too fast for Vader to grab a hold of it.|The flashback concludes with Obi-Wan taking Anakinâ€™s lightsaber with the force and telling him that heâ€™s a great warrior, but his need to prove himself is his undoing. Until then, a padawan you will still be. As it shows Anakinâ€™s immense disappointment in himself. As we get a shot from Anakin to Vader, showing exactly how he feels in this moment. |As Reva tries to take him out from behind, he senses it and freezes her with the force, just like Fallen Order when he fought the second sister and Cal Kestis. He toys with her, completely making her look like a joke as he doesnâ€™t even bother to use his lightsaber, as sheâ€™s not worthy of him using it. Vader just uses the force until he takes hers and splits it in two, throwing the other half to her feet. Besting her in lightsaber combat without even putting any effort into it. As she drops her to her knees he summons both sabers and for a moment I thought he was going to end her like how Anakin Skywalker did to Dooku, however he didnâ€™t do that. He stood over her and plunged the saber into her, just as Anakin plunged it into her as a youngling. Now I watched this scene over and over again to confirm that he did indeed stab young Reva. We see her as a youngling make a face of pain as Anakin plunges it only to be connected to Vader finishing the movement. The first person POV of her keeling over dizzy as Anakin stands over her, is enough for me to believe the way this was shot and directed, is to imply that she was indeed stabbed as a youngling, just not fatally. Vader tells her that he knew all along that she was the youngling.|Join this channel to get access to perks:|https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC8CbFnDTYkiVweaz8y9wd_Q/join|Become a Patron to support future content - https://www.patreon.com/StarWarsTheory

title: For peace we need weapons, Ukraine's ex-President Poroshenko tells DW | DW News
description: Former Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko, who was in office from 2014 until 2019, called on Germany and other countries in Europe to stand "shoulder to shoulder" with Ukraine.|"For the peace, we need three things: weapons, weapons and weapons," Poroshenko told DW from Kyiv.|He added that securing an end to Russia's invasion in Ukraine was "vital for the future of Europe."|Poroshenko also defended his decision to sign the Minsk agreement with Russia, saying the 2015 peace accord won Ukraine "eight years to create [an] army" and rebuild its economy.|"We win eight years to continue the reforms and to move to the European Union," he said.|The agreement was aimed at ending fighting between Russia-backed separatists and Ukrainian forces in the eastern Donbas region â€” where fighting with Russian troops is currently concentrated.|Subscribe: https://www.youtube.com/user/deutschewelleenglish?sub_confirmation=1|For more news go to: http://www.dw.com/en/|Follow DW on social media:|â–ºFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/deutschewellenews/|â–ºTwitter: https://twitter.com/dwnews|â–ºInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/dwnews|FÃ¼r Videos in deutscher Sprache besuchen Sie: https://www.youtube.com/dwdeutsch|#Ukraine #Russia #Poroshenko

title: Inside Al Shabaab: The extremist group trying to seize Somalia
description: For more than fifteen years the extremist group Al Shabaab has been fighting a bloody insurgency in Somalia.|||(Subscribe: https://bit.ly/C4_News_Subscribe)||Now, as President Biden redeploys American troops to the country, are the group winning the fight?|Formed in 2002, by 2008 they controlled much of southern Somalia. |They soon pledged allegiance to Al Qaeda and began conducting attacks at home and abroad.|In September 2013 they killed nearly 70 people in the Westgate shopping mall attack in Kenya's capital Nairobi.|Then again in Kenya in April 2015 Al Shabaab militants killed 148 people at Garissa University College.|Back home in the Somali capital Mogadishu they carried out their most deadly attack in October 2017, killing more than five hundred people in a massive truck bombing.|In the years that have followed, the group's attacks have become routine. |They often kill dozens of civilians a month, as they battle the African Union troops there to try and keep them at bay.|Now emboldened by the Taliban takeover of Afghanistan following the US withdrawal, the group are cementing control of their territory, with the aim to take the whole country and implement strict Sharia law.|At the moment, Al Shabaab control vast swathes of central and southern Somalia but their reach spreads far further, with Somali government control diminishing.|Our correspondent Jamal Osman obtained rare access to film in Al Shabaab territory and travelled to their de facto capital Jilib.|------------------|Get more news at our site - https://www.channel4.com/news/ ||||Follow us:||Facebook - https://www.facebook.com/Channel4News/||Twitter - https://twitter.com/Channel4News

title: Why Recessions May Be Inevitable
description: America has experienced at least 30 recessions throughout history, dating back as early as 1857. Some experts believe that they have become an inevitable part of the economic cycle that fluctuates between periods of expansion and contraction. Nonetheless, certain measures can still be taken to make recessions less likely. As the nationâ€™s authority on monetary policies, the Federal Reserve plays a critical role in managing recessions. So why do recessions happen and what can the Fed do about it? Watch the video to find out.|The U.S. has experienced at least 30 recessions throughout history, dating back as early as 1857.|Some economists argue that they may have become an inevitable part of the financial cycle that fluctuates between periods of expansion and contraction.|â€œHistory teaches us that recessions are inevitable,â€ said David Wessel, a senior fellow in economic studies at The Brookings Institution. â€œI think there are things we can do with a policy that makes recessions less likely or when they occur, less severe. Weâ€™ve learned a lot, but we havenâ€™t learned enough to say that weâ€™re never going to have another recession.â€|As the nationâ€™s authority on monetary policies, the Federal Reserve plays a critical role in managing recessions.|The Fed is currently attempting to avoid a recession by engineering whatâ€™s known as a â€œsoft landing,â€ in which incremental interest rate hikes are used to curb inflation without pushing the economy into recession.|â€œWhat theyâ€™re trying to do is raise rates enough so demand slows,â€ said Jason Snipe, chief investment officer at Odyssey Capital Advisors.|But a successful soft landing is extremely rare as the monetary policy needed to slow down the economy is often enforced too late to make any meaningful impact.|It was arguably achieved just once, in 1994, thanks to the Fedâ€™s more proactive response to inflation and good timing.|â€³[Itâ€™s] really, really difficult to get into that really, really narrow zone,â€ said Stephen Miran, former senior advisor at the U.S. Department of Treasury. â€œItâ€™s the difference between trying to land an airplane in a really wide and spacious open field versus trying to land an airplane on a very, very narrow piece of land with rocks and water on either side.â€|Some experts also argue that policies have a limitation on what they can achieve against an impending downturn.|â€œPolicy tends to operate with long lags, which means the ability to effect immediate change in the economy is quite slow. I also think that increasingly we live in a global economy where the cross-currents that are impacting the economic dynamics are very complex,â€ said Lisa Shalett, chief investment officer, wealth management at Morgan Stanley.|â€œThese are dynamics that the Fed doesnâ€™t have the tools to address and so to a certain extent, we do think that policymakers have certainly developed more tools to fight recessions,â€ she said. â€œBut we donâ€™t think that you can rely on policymakers to prevent recessionsâ€|Â» Subscribe to CNBC: https://cnb.cx/SubscribeCNBC|Â» Subscribe to CNBC TV: https://cnb.cx/SubscribeCNBCtelevision|About CNBC: From 'Wall Street' to 'Main Street' to award winning original documentaries and Reality TV series, CNBC has you covered. title: Empat Bus Rombongan Kader Partai NasDem Alami Kecelakaan Beruntun di Tol Japek
description: KOMPAS.TV - Empat bus rombongan Kader Partai Nasdem Asal Jawa Timur alami kecelakaan beruntun di ruas Tol Jakarta Cikampek, Kota Bekasi, Jawa Barat, pada Rabu (15/06) pagi tadi.||||Rombongan ini hendak menuju jakarta untuk mengikuti rapat kerja nasional di Senayan.||||Baca Juga Terungkap Kecelakaan di Bekasi Cuma Sandiwara, Rekayasa Ditabrak demi Klaim Asuransi Rp3 Miliar di https://www.kompas.tv/article/296432/terungkap-kecelakaan-di-bekasi-cuma-sandiwara-rekayasa-ditabrak-demi-klaim-asuransi-rp3-miliar||||Kemacetan panjang di ruas Tol Jakarta Cikampek arah Jakarta di kilometer 7, Jatibening, Kota Bekasi, Rabu pagi ini terjadi akibat kecelakaan beruntun empat bus rombongan kader Partai Nasdem asal Jawa Timur.||||Mereka berasal dari Kabupaten Kota Madiun, Mojokerto, Ngawi, Jombang, dan Nganjuk.||||Rombongan ini hendak menuju Jakarta untuk mengikuti rapat kerja nasional di Senayan.||||Kecelakaan ini terjadi diduga akibat sang supir bus yang paling depan yang melakukan rem mendadak. Karena kondisi jalan tengah padat tabarakan beruntun pun tak bisa dihindari.||||Empat bus yang dievakuasi ke badan jalan mengalami rusak berat dibagian depan seperti kaca dan bemper ringsek.||||Salah satu sopir bus sempat terjepit dibagian kemudi, namun sudah dievakuasi ke rumah sakit terdekat. Beberapa penumpang sempat terkena serpihan pecahan kaca.||||Akibat peristiwa ini sempat terjadi kemacetan diruas Tol Jakarta Cikampek arah Jakarta.||||Petugas Jasamarga langsung melakukan evakuasi kendaraan dengan melakukan penderekan. Kecelakaan tersebut kini ditangani petugas lalu lintas PJR Tol Japek.||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/299479/empat-bus-rombongan-kader-partai-nasdem-alami-kecelakaan-beruntun-di-tol-japek

title: 'No money for chai': Pak citizens fume after govt asked them to reduce tea consumption
description: Cash-strapped Pakistan government has urged people to cut down the consumption of tea as sipping fewer cups a day would help reduce the import bill eating into the nation's depleting foreign exchange reserves. The appeal from Federal Minister for Planning Ahsan Iqbal came after it emerged that Pakistan consumed tea worth Rs 83.88 billion (USD 400 million) in the fiscal year 2021-22. Iqbalâ€™s appeal to cut down the consumption of tea by one to two cups did not go down well with people as they started criticising him on social media. title: Rumah Nikita Mirzani di Pesanggrahan Jakarta Selatan Didatangi Polisi
description: PESANGGRAHAN, KOMPAS.TV - Rumah selebritas Nikita Mirzani di Pesanggrahan, Jakarta Selatan, didatangi sejumlah Penyidik Satreskrim Polres Serang Kota, Rabu (15/06) dini hari.||||Kedatangan polisi untuk menjemput paksa Nikita Mirzani dalam kasus pencemaran nama baik, dengan pelapor Mahendra Dito.||||Nikita Mirzani menyoroti tindakan petugas yang sempat memaksa masuk rumahnya.||||Baca Juga Gubernur Ganjar Pranowo Resmikan SMAN Tawangmangu di Kaki Gunung Lawu di https://www.kompas.tv/article/299497/gubernur-ganjar-pranowo-resmikan-sman-tawangmangu-di-kaki-gunung-lawu||||Sebelum akan dijemput paksa, Nikita Mirzani menyebut dirinya telah menerima 12 kali surat panggilan pemeriksaan.||||Namun, pada Rabu (15/06) sore, selebritas Nikita Mirzani akhirnya memenuhi panggilan Penyidik Polresta Serang kota.||||Didampingi pengacaranya, Nikita Mirzani datang sekitar pukul 15.00 WIB sore.||||Ia menjalani pemeriksaan sebagai saksi atas undang-undang informasi dan transaksi elektronik, terkait konten yang diunggah pada instagram storynya.||||Dalam proses pemeriksaan, Nikita menerima sekitar 30 pertanyaan dari penyidik.||||Baca Juga Ketua KPU, Artis, hingga Duta Wisata Indonesia Bahas Pemilihan Umum dan Generasi Muda di https://www.kompas.tv/article/299493/ketua-kpu-artis-hingga-duta-wisata-indonesia-bahas-pemilihan-umum-dan-generasi-muda||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/299505/rumah-nikita-mirzani-di-pesanggrahan-jakarta-selatan-didatangi-polisi

title: 'Destructive role': J&K govt bans schools run by Jamaat-e-Islami over Kashmir unrest
description: More than 300 educational institutions run by Falah-e-Aam (FAT), an affiliate of banned Jamaat-e-Islami, have been stopped from operating by the Jammu and Kashmir School education department. PTI reported that an order was passed by School Education Secretary B K Singh on Monday directing cessation of academic activities in FAT-affiliated schools and also asked chief education officers of various districts to seal the institutions within 15 days in consultation with the district administration. The order also said that all the students studying in these banned institutions shall admit themselves to nearby government schools for the current session. title: Momen Mesra Jokowi Jalan Bareng Para Ketum Partai Sebelum Reshuffle Kabinet, Sempat Atur Barisan
description: JAKARTA, KOMPAS.TV - Presiden Joko Widodo (Jokowi) terlihat berjalan bersama para ketua umum (ketum) partai sebelum reshuffle kabinet di Istana Negara, pada Rabu (15/6) siang.||||Jokowi berjalan di antara ketua umum Partai Nasdem Surya Paloh dan ketua umum PDIP Megawati.||||Sebelumnya, Jokowi sempat mengatur barisan agar dirinya dapat berjalan beriringan. ||Tampak hadir berbagai ketua umum partai dari mulai Prabowo Subianto hingga Ketua Umum Partai Amanat Nasional (PAN) Zulkifli Hasan. ||||Baca Juga Alasan Jokowi Tunjuk Eks Panglima TNI Hadi Tjahjanto Jadi Menteri ATR: Kerjanya Sangat Detail di https://www.kompas.tv/article/299443/alasan-jokowi-tunjuk-eks-panglima-tni-hadi-tjahjanto-jadi-menteri-atr-kerjanya-sangat-detail||||Untuk diketahui, Presiden Joko Widodo telah melantik sejumlah menteri dan wakil menteri baru, yakni Zulkifli Hasan sebagai Menteri Perdagangan, Hadi Tjahjanto sebagai Menteri ATR/BPN. ||||Adapun wakil menteri baru yakni Raja Juli Antoni sebagai Wakil Menteri ATR/BPN, Wempi Watimpo sebagai Wakil Menteri Dalam Negeri serta Afriansyah Noor sebagai Wakil Menteri Ketenagakerjaan.||||Video Editor: Arief Rahman||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/299449/momen-mesra-jokowi-jalan-bareng-para-ketum-partai-sebelum-reshuffle-kabinet-sempat-atur-barisan
